<span class="avatar"></span>
<span class="comment_num"><a href="#comment-486" title="Permalink to this comment" rel="nofollow">1</a></span>
<span class="comment_author">Anonymous (of course)</span>
<span class="comment_time">October 5, 2010 at 3:31 am</span>

					</dt>
					<dd class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-486">
<p>I&#8217;m one of those unfortunate beings who is not just under illegal and unjustified surveillance, but I am also constantly hacked and apparently have been experimented on (social engineering, use of electromagnetic something, trauma conditioning, surveillance with feedback, extreme harassment, false accusations, etc. &#8211; straight out of psy ops manuals) for quite some time.  Other members of my family may be unwitting victims also.</p>
<p>The problems are those that you delineate &#8211; no justice (I have evidence for much of my harassment and hacking and nothing is being done though I finally got a case number).  Worse, people with my problems are shuffled off into groups that badly describe the harassment sources and lead to paranoid thinking and political actions unrelated to the problem at hand.</p>
<p>I think that accountability is necessary.  I&#8217;m not interested in becoming the poster child for non consensual experiments or have to spend 10 years of my life duking it out in court.  In fact, I want to live out the tatters of my life as I see fit elsewhere.  (And the truth is, I am unsure which particular agency should get the lawsuit since the case isn&#8217;t being investigated as it should be by the proper agencies.)</p>
<p>To what extent does this accountability need to be linked to the politics of extremists I don&#8217;t know.  It seems like those with some power who know that these abuses are going on should risk themselves and come out about what is going on&#8230; but it appears that there is a preference to use this abuse to forward various types of political causes that will ultimately benefit the harassers and no one else.</p>
<p>I don&#8217;t care what the *benefits* of this harassment, surveillance and experimentation are:  national security?, more information for the neuroscientists?  Who knows.  If the agency behind this came and told me how it would be good for society that I suffer like this, I could easily win that debate with them.  But I&#8217;m not given the opportunity to &#8211; the malignant narcissists and sociopaths with the salaries are the ones making those decisions.</p>
</div>
					</dd>
